## 9. Documentary References

The project's irregularity vocabulary is sourced from these analog references:

- **Hiroshi Sugimoto's seascapes** — slow drift, breath, near-stillness with imperceptible variation.
- **Wim Wenders' "Wings of Desire" cinematography** — non-perfect framing, on-the-shoulder breath.
- **Roger Deakins' lighting in "Sicario"** — vignette weight that crushes asymmetrically.
- **Sebastião Salgado's silver gelatin prints** — grain that has age, depth, and warmth.
- **Christopher Doyle's handheld work** — deliberately imperfect motion that reads as human.
- **Apartamento Magazine layouts** — copy that breathes off-baseline; images that sit slightly off-grid.
- **Aperture Magazine print runs** — paper imperfections embraced, never corrected.

---

## 10. Forbidden Patterns

### Hyper-perfection
- ❌ Identical stagger gaps (always exactly 80ms).
- ❌ Identical reveal durations across a cluster (every line exactly 720ms).
- ❌ Reveal y-offsets all set to the same value (always exactly 8%).
- ❌ Atmosphere parameters identical across all scenes in a chapter.
- ❌ Hover-in and hover-out durations symmetrical.

### Robotic synchronization
- ❌ All elements in a viewport revealing on the **exact** same scroll progress trigger.
- ❌ Multiple breathing loops sharing the same period (`8s` everywhere).
- ❌ Chapter transitions starting at exactly the same scroll position every time.
- ❌ Uniform light leak intensity across an entire scene.

### Over-smoothed motion
- ❌ Continuous lerp without any sub-amplitude jitter.
- ❌ Atmospheric shaders that loop perfectly (period `n × π`).
- ❌ Scroll-velocity reactions with no delay layer.

### Sterile transitions
- ❌ Chapter transitions that crossfade with no atmosphere drift.
- ❌ Route transitions with mathematically perfect blur curves.
- ❌ Hero intros with no human delay before motion begins.

### Excessive consistency
- ❌ Identical text reveal across all chapters.
- ❌ Same vignette intensity in every scene.
- ❌ Cursor lerp identical regardless of state.

### Fake sophistication
- ❌ Random parameters dressed up as "design" (the antithesis of this system — **all variance is bounded and seeded**).
- ❌ "Glitch" effects, datamosh, faux-VHS — these are **performance of imperfection**, not imperfection.
- ❌ "Brutalist" type with intentionally awkward kerning — that is **affectation**, not humanity.
- ❌ "Lo-fi" aesthetic overlays (vinyl crackle, CRT scanlines) — costume, not character.

